{
  "id": "019d3290-1eaa-7191-ab10-6d45f3d8c9dd",
  "content": "# Composable Retrieval Pipeline (Phase 1 of BM25 Hybrid Search)\n\n## Decision\nRefactored the monolithic `GraphExpandRetriever` into a 4-stage composable pipeline:\nSearcher -> Fusion -> Expander -> Reranker. Each stage is behind an async trait.\nThe pipeline implements the existing `Retriever` trait as a drop-in replacement.\n\n## Architecture\n- `NormalizedScore` newtype with Eq/Ord (NaN excluded by construction)\n- `ComponentRegistry<T>` generic factory pattern for plug-and-play components\n- `PipelineConfig` in `[rag.pipeline]` TOML section with backward-compatible fallback\n- Single-searcher fast path avoids tokio::spawn overhead for the common case\n- Query embedding wrapped in Arc and shared across stages (no redundant clones)\n\n## Key Design Decisions\n- PassThrough fusion applies min-max normalization. This changes scores vs legacy path,\n  but compatibility test confirms >=80% entry ID overlap across queries.\n- Graph expander is NOT in the ComponentRegistry because it requires config-driven alpha.\n  It is constructed directly in `build_pipeline_retriever`.\n- Legacy `VectorRetriever` and `GraphExpandRetriever` are marked `#[deprecated]`.\n- `RetrievalMetrics` extended with optional fields (bm25_latency_ms, fusion_method, etc.)\n  that serialize only when present, preserving API backward compatibility.\n\n## Extension Points for Phase 2+\n- Phase 2a: Add `Bm25Searcher` implementing `Searcher` trait, register in PipelineRegistry\n- Phase 2b: Same pattern for PostgresStore tsvector\n- Phase 2c: Implement `Fusion` trait as \"rrf\" (RRF), register in PipelineRegistry\n- Phase 3: ArcSwap hot-swap on the pipeline for runtime A/B benchmarking\n\n## Files\n- `crates/corvia-kernel/src/pipeline/` (6 new files: mod, core, searcher, fusion, expander, registry)\n- `crates/corvia-common/src/config.rs` (PipelineConfig, RrfConfig, Bm25Config)\n\nPR: #55, Closes #38",
